The following is an informal TODO list for jsqsh:

- Create a "bestfit" display style that will attempt to fit the results to
  the console window size.
- [Done] Semicolon termination for PL/SQL - Here's my thoughts:
    If the terminator is a semicolon...
       If the current SQL contains
          BEGIN (but not BEGIN TRANSACTION)
          END
          DECLARE
          EXCEPTION
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] TYPE [BODY]
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] TRIGGER
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] CONTEXT
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] FUNCTION
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] PACKAGE [BODY]
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] PACKAGE 
          CREATE [OR REPLACE] PROCEDURE 
       then
          a semicolon on a line by itself is a "go"
          a double semicolon at the end (";;" is a "go")
       else
          the semicolon is a "go"




